===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|NL.|rachis}}, from {{der|en|grc|ῥάχις||spine, ridge}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|en|/ˈɹeɪkɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|+|rachides}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete|zoology|anatomy}} The [[spinal column]], or the [[vertebrae]] of the spine. {{defdate|17th-19th c.}}
# {{lb|en|zoology}} An anatomical [[shaft]] or [[axis]] in a marine [[invertebrate]]. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Danna Staaf|title=Squid Empire|publisher=ForeEdge|year=2017|isbn=9781611689235|page=115|passage=In some squid species, the pen '''rachis''' flares out into wings on either side, and the tip of the '''rachis''' grows into a thick cone.}}
# {{lb|en|ornithology}} The [[central]] shaft of a [[feather]]. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
# {{lb|en|botany}} The main [[shaft]] of either a [[compound]] [[leaf]], [[head]] of [[grain]], or fern [[frond]]. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}

